### A Statement from Measure Theory

Let $X$ be an open subset of $\mathbf{R}$, and let $\Omega$ be a [measure space](/Measure_space). Suppose $f: X \times \Omega \to \mathbf{R}$ satisfies the following conditions: [6] [7] [2]

*   For each $x \in X$, $f(x, \omega)$ is a Lebesgue-integrable function of $\omega$.
*   For [almost all](/Almost_all) $\omega \in \Omega$, the partial derivative $f_x$ exists for all $x \in X$.
*   There exists an integrable function $\theta: \Omega \to \mathbf{R}$ such that $|f_x(x, \omega)| \leq \theta(\omega)$ for all $x \in X$ and almost every $\omega \in \Omega$.

